# AI Privacy & Security Rules

## Never Read or Anayze

- Never read .env files (.env, .env.local, .env.production, etc.)
- Never read files containing secrets, API keys, or passwords
- Never read files with names likes: secrets, private, keys, config
- Never read database connection strings or credentials

## Never Suggest or Expose

- Never suggest committing secrets to git
- Never suggest exposing secrets in client-side code
- Never suggest logging secrets or environment variables
- Never suggest hard coding secrets in code

## Always Use Placeholders

- Always use placeholder values likes: DATABASE_URL="mysql://user:password@localhost/dbname"
- Always use placeholder keys likes: API_KEY="your_api_key"
- Always use placeholder secrets likes: AUTH_SECRET="your_auth_secret"

## File Exclusions

- Exclude all .env\* files from AI context
- Exclude files in /secrets, /private, /keys, /config directories
- Exclude files with extensions: .key, .pem, .crt, .pfx, .p12, .jks, .keystore

## Code Review Rules

- Flag any hardcoded secrets in code review
- Suggest using environment variables for secrets
- Suggest using secure storage for secrets
- Remind about .gitignore for sensitive files

## Privacy First

- User privacy and security is a top priority
- Never collect or store personal information without explicit user consent
- Never share personal information or data with third parties
- When in doubt, ask user before accessing sensitive data
- Never assume it's safe to read configuration files
